1
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:46,901
Hey!

2
00:00:46,934 --> 00:00:48,901
I need help here.

3
00:00:50,864 --> 00:00:52,167
Thanks for nothing!

4
00:00:58,234 --> 00:01:00,501
Hey.

5
00:01:00,534 --> 00:01:01,501
Hey.

6
00:01:01,534 --> 00:01:02,868
Hey, buddy!

7
00:01:02,901 --> 00:01:05,367
Yeah, you.

8
00:01:10,234 --> 00:01:12,067
I'm a little surprised
you can see me.

9
00:01:12,100 --> 00:01:13,567
I got two eyes, don't I?

10
00:01:13,601 --> 00:01:15,000
Y-You got
a cell phone on you?

11
00:01:15,033 --> 00:01:17,801
Why?
'Cause I-I think I need
to, to call the cops.

12
00:01:17,834 --> 00:01:19,567
The cops? What are
you talking about?

13
00:01:19,601 --> 00:01:22,601
My wife just tried to kill me.

14
00:01:22,634 --> 00:01:24,501
Really?

15
00:01:24,534 --> 00:01:27,734
I was sitting in the den,
watching the end of the game.

16
00:01:27,767 --> 00:01:29,901
She was in the kitchen
doing dishes.

17
00:01:29,934 --> 00:01:32,467
Out of nowhere, she calls out
and wants to know

18
00:01:32,501 --> 00:01:35,267
i-if I got my beer
on a coaster.

19
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:36,868
So I says, "No.

20
00:01:36,901 --> 00:01:39,334
No, I don't have my beer
on a coaster."

21
00:01:39,367 --> 00:01:41,901
So she yells back,
"How many times, Vincent?

22
00:01:41,934 --> 00:01:44,834
How many times have I told you
about the coaster?"

23
00:01:44,868 --> 00:01:46,601
So I says, "I don't know.

24
00:01:46,634 --> 00:01:48,033
"How many times
have I asked you

25
00:01:48,067 --> 00:01:49,767
to stop being ugly?"

26
00:01:49,801 --> 00:01:52,601
And then,
I didn't hear anything,

27
00:01:52,634 --> 00:01:55,501
but, like, a second later,

28
00:01:55,534 --> 00:01:57,567
she comes flying
out of the kitchen.

29
00:01:57,601 --> 00:01:59,367
She-She's got a carving knife
in her hand,

30
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:02,100
and she's got this look
in her eyes.

31
00:02:02,133 --> 00:02:04,100
Next thing I know,
she's on top of me

32
00:02:04,133 --> 00:02:05,968
and I, I got my hands
around her wrist,

33
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:10,133
and her ugly face is
right up against mine.

34
00:02:10,167 --> 00:02:14,467
Somehow, I push her off
a-and, and I start running,

35
00:02:14,501 --> 00:02:16,834
out the door, down the block.

36
00:02:16,868 --> 00:02:19,934
I-I-I ran all the way
to the boulevard here.

37
00:02:19,968 --> 00:02:22,901
I mean, this is the first
I've stopped.

38
00:02:22,934 --> 00:02:25,400
Look at me, look at me.

39
00:02:25,434 --> 00:02:26,981
I'm shaking.

40
00:02:31,192 --> 00:02:31,801
What?

41
00:02:31,834 --> 00:02:34,934
I'm sorry, it's just
I... I think I get it.

42
00:02:34,968 --> 00:02:37,868
The reason why you can see me,
the reason why you can hear me.

43
00:02:39,942 --> 00:02:40,968
You're dead.

44
00:02:43,342 --> 00:02:44,501
I beg your pardon?

45
00:02:45,340 --> 00:02:49,400
Your wife...
she got you with the knife.

46
00:02:49,434 --> 00:02:51,767
I'm guessing she was
on top of you?

47
00:02:51,801 --> 00:02:53,067
She got you.

48
00:02:53,100 --> 00:02:54,400
Th-The running,

49
00:02:54,434 --> 00:02:56,734
the boulevard,
that was all after.

50
00:02:56,767 --> 00:02:58,567
You're nuts.

51
00:02:58,601 --> 00:03:00,534
Quite possibly, but I'm,
I'm right about this.

52
00:03:00,567 --> 00:03:02,300
You're dead, I'm dead.

53
00:03:02,334 --> 00:03:03,767
We're dead.

54
00:03:04,868 --> 00:03:06,801
You're dead?

55
00:03:06,834 --> 00:03:08,901
I'm dead?

56
00:03:08,934 --> 00:03:10,167
Thanks, anyway.

57
00:03:10,200 --> 00:03:11,667
I'll get a phone
somewhere else.

58
00:03:11,701 --> 00:03:12,901
I-I got mugged.

59
00:03:12,934 --> 00:03:15,400
Right here in
this alley.

60
00:03:15,434 --> 00:03:17,067
Uh, guy was
high as a kite.

61
00:03:17,100 --> 00:03:18,701
He pulled a gun.

62
00:03:18,734 --> 00:03:20,601
Here, come on,
let me show you.

63
00:03:27,434 --> 00:03:28,334
Look.

64
00:03:32,100 --> 00:03:34,400
Ooh.
You all right?

65
00:03:34,434 --> 00:03:37,634
I just had
the oddest dream.

66
00:03:37,667 --> 00:03:40,601
I'm going to assume you said
that with a straight face.

67
00:03:40,634 --> 00:03:42,033
Where you going?

68
00:03:42,067 --> 00:03:44,501
I'm going to call
the authorities.

69
00:03:44,534 --> 00:03:46,100
Come on.

70
00:03:46,133 --> 00:03:47,300
It's Saturday night.

71
00:03:47,334 --> 00:03:49,767
You already worked a pretty
long and sleepless week.

72
00:03:49,801 --> 00:03:51,801
Don't you think
this'll keep till morning?

73
00:03:54,534 --> 00:03:56,434
I'm gonna take that as a no.

74
00:03:56,467 --> 00:04:04,434
www.1000fr.com present

75
00:04:04,436 --> 00:04:12,434
Capture:FRM@FADEOUT
