I'm the only one.

260
00:12:45,789 --> 00:12:48,357
Actually, I'm with the
District Attorney's office.

261
00:12:48,389 --> 00:12:50,190
And I want to take
this opportunity

262
00:12:50,223 --> 00:12:52,990
to assure you we are
going to find the person

263
00:12:53,023 --> 00:12:54,357
who did this to you.

264
00:12:54,389 --> 00:12:57,689
We are going to punish the
person who did this to you.

265
00:12:59,756 --> 00:13:01,956
You know, it's okay
if you don't.

266
00:13:03,990 --> 00:13:06,156
Excuse me?

267
00:13:07,218 --> 00:13:10,075
I got to believe you've got
better things to do.

268
00:13:10,257 --> 00:13:14,090
I mean, you find the person
that did this to me,

269
00:13:14,123 --> 00:13:15,723
it's not going
to change anything.

270
00:13:15,756 --> 00:13:17,522
I'm still
going to be dead.

271
00:13:17,556 --> 00:13:20,190
You deserve justice,
Mr. Turley.

272
00:13:20,223 --> 00:13:21,823
And we certainly
don't want

273
00:13:21,856 --> 00:13:23,923
whoever did this to
you to do it again.

274
00:13:23,956 --> 00:13:25,257
Oh, I wouldn't worry
about that.

275
00:13:25,290 --> 00:13:26,456
I don't think he would.

276
00:13:28,090 --> 00:13:31,456
I got the distinct impression
that this was a one-time thing.

277
00:13:34,522 --> 00:13:39,623
Well, on the off-chance
that you're wrong,

278
00:13:39,656 --> 00:13:41,856
is there anything
you can tell me

279
00:13:41,890 --> 00:13:43,890
about this man?

280
00:13:49,026 --> 00:13:50,526
He rebuffed you?

281
00:13:50,527 --> 00:13:51,594
He rebuffed me.

282
00:13:51,627 --> 00:13:52,826
I looked down
for a second

283
00:13:52,859 --> 00:13:54,260
to get something
out of my purse,

284
00:13:54,293 --> 00:13:55,493
and he was gone.

285
00:13:55,527 --> 00:13:56,793
The nerve of some ghosts.

286
00:13:56,826 --> 00:13:58,793
He looked so threatened,

287
00:13:58,826 --> 00:14:01,360
like I was some kind
of problem or something.

288
00:14:02,187 --> 00:14:03,653
Well, who knows?

289
00:14:03,686 --> 00:14:04,786
Maybe he was embarrassed.

290
00:14:04,820 --> 00:14:06,187
Embarrassed by what?

291
00:14:06,220 --> 00:14:10,452
Well, the guy's at his
own memorial service.

292
00:14:10,486 --> 00:14:12,653
He's spying on his friends,

293
00:14:12,686 --> 00:14:15,120
listening to what they
had to say about him.

294
00:14:15,153 --> 00:14:17,452
It's a little narcissistic,
it's a little embarrassing

295
00:14:17,486 --> 00:14:18,686
if you get caught at it.

296
00:14:18,719 --> 00:14:20,553
I just wanted him to know
that I cared.

297
00:14:20,586 --> 00:14:21,786
I just want him
to know

298
00:14:21,820 --> 00:14:23,419
that whoever did this
to him

299
00:14:23,452 --> 00:14:25,220
wasn't simply going
to get away with it.

300
00:14:25,253 --> 00:14:26,719
All right, I
get that, I do,

301
00:14:26,753 --> 00:14:28,220
and I'm sure
that he does, too,

302
00:14:28,253 --> 00:14:29,853
so just be patient.

303
00:14:29,886 --> 00:14:31,287
If he really wants your help,

304
00:14:31,319 --> 00:14:34,053
I'm sure he'll
come asking for it.

305
00:14:34,086 --> 00:14:36,120
I certainly would
if I were dead.

306
00:14:38,719 --> 00:14:41,352
She really did it.

307
00:14:41,386 --> 00:14:42,920
I'm sorry.

308
00:14:42,953 --> 00:14:45,220
I just thought...

309
00:14:45,253 --> 00:14:47,108
you seemed like you really
needed to see the truth.

310
00:14:47,208 --> 00:14:49,386
It seemed like you were having
a hard time accepting.

311
00:14:49,419 --> 00:14:50,686
Oh.

312
00:14:50,719 --> 00:14:52,486
My grandfath's watch.

313
00:14:52,519 --> 00:14:54,519
Killing me wasn't enough.

314
00:14:54,553 --> 00:14:57,352
She had to make me
break that watch.

315
00:14:57,386 --> 00:14:59,287
This watch?

316
00:14:59,319 --> 00:15:01,886
This is a hundred-
year-old watch.

317
00:15:01,920 --> 00:15:04,753
My Grandpa DiScala,
he gave it to me

318
00:15:04,786 --> 00:15:07,519
on his deathbed.

319
00:15:08,986 --> 00:15:10,419
Let it go, Vincent.

320
00:15:10,452 --> 00:15:12,786
We don't need watches
where we're going.

321
00:15:15,053 --> 00:15:16,287
Why, Gladys?!

322
00:15:22,352 --> 00:15:25,287
All right, I know
you hated me,

323
00:15:25,319 --> 00:15:27,187
but I never knew you
hated me this much.

324
00:15:35,853 --> 00:15:38,220
You know...

325
00:15:38,253 --> 00:15:40,086
for a fellow
murder victim,

326
00:15:40,120 --> 00:15:43,053
you're being pretty Zen
about all this.

327
00:15:44,086 --> 00:15:45,519
I'm dead.

328
00:15:45,553 --> 00:15:46,786
Why shouldn't I be Zen?

329
00:15:46,820 --> 00:15:48,086
Aren't you ticked?

330
00:15:48,120 --> 00:15:49,820
Don't you want to get
the guy who killed you?

331
00:15:49,853 --> 00:15:52,953
I'm beyond all that now;
you should be, too.

332
00:15:58,153 --> 00:16:00,220
What happened to you, anyway?

333
00:16:00,253 --> 00:16:01,352
Mugging, huh?

334
00:16:01,386 --> 00:16:06,586
Well... um, not exactly.

335
00:16:06,619 --> 00:16:08,686
What do you mean,
"not exactly"?

336
00:16:08,719 --> 00:16:10,719
How'd you end up getting
shot in that alley?

337
00:16:10,753 --> 00:16:13,786
I... it's kind of a...

338
00:16:13,820 --> 00:16:16,653
a long story actually.

339
00:16:16,686 --> 00:16:19,220
Look at me, friend.

340
00:16:19,253 --> 00:16:22,086
I got nothing but time, right?

341
00:16:22,120 --> 00:16:23,352
You know what?

342
00:16:23,386 --> 00:16:25,686
I'd rather show you
than tell you.

343
00:16:25,719 --> 00:16:27,586
We have to go
somewhere else now?

344
00:16:27,619 --> 00:16:29,786
My apartment, yeah.

345
00:16:37,419 --> 00:16:39,020
Uh, seriously,
Vincent...

346
00:16:39,053 --> 00:16:41,020
I'm not sure
that you want to see this.

347
00:16:47,653 --> 00:16:50,786
Oh... all
right, fine.

348
00:16:50,820 --> 00:16:52,820
Your apartment, it is.

349
00:16:59,486 --> 00:17:01,619
Vincent and Gladys DiScala.

350
00:17:01,653 --> 00:17:03,187
Got it.

351
00:17:03,220 --> 00:17:04,753
Anything else?

352
00:17:04,786 --> 00:17:07,586
She cut him up with a saw;
that's why we can't find him.

353
00:17:07,619 --> 00:17:09,120
No way to get a warrant,

354
00:17:09,153 --> 00:17:11,386
but once I have an address,
I could certainly swing by

355
00:17:11,419 --> 00:17:13,419
and ask a few questions
about her husband's whereabouts.

356
00:17:13,452 --> 00:17:14,786
You want to come with?

357
00:17:14,820 --> 00:17:16,120
Can't.

358
00:17:16,153 --> 00:17:17,586
I'm on my way
to Morgan Turley's apartment.

359
00:17:17,619 --> 00:17:18,920
What for?

360
00:17:18,953 --> 00:17:21,386
Well, in that same dream,
Morgan started to suggest

361
00:17:21,419 --> 00:17:24,120
that maybe there was more
to it than just a mugging.

362
00:17:24,153 --> 00:17:27,586
And then he said
he'd rather show Vincent

363
00:17:27,619 --> 00:17:29,686
why he was killed than tell him.

364
00:17:29,719 --> 00:17:32,419
He made it sound like the answer
was somewhere in his apartment.

365
00:17:32,452 --> 00:17:33,820
I just...

366
00:17:33,853 --> 00:17:35,319
I just want to take a look.

367
00:18:01,653 --> 00:18:04,486
Hey, kitty, kitty.

368
00:18:04,519 --> 00:18:07,719
Oh, kitty.

369
00:18:19,586 --> 00:18:22,786
Can I help you
with something?

370
00:18:22,820 --> 00:18:24,953
Hello again.

371
00:18:24,986 --> 00:18:26,287
Hello.

372
00:18:26,452 --> 00:18:28,753
Is there something
I can help you with?

373
00:18:28,786 --> 00:18:31,753
I was just looking
at this chair.

374
00:18:31,786 --> 00:18:34,320
I was wondering why it was
pointing towards the window.

375
00:18:34,353 --> 00:18:36,486
I like looking
out the window.

376
00:18:36,519 --> 00:18:38,020
I've always liked
looking out the window,

377
00:18:38,053 --> 00:18:39,619
ever since
I was a little boy.

378
00:18:39,653 --> 00:18:41,486
Anything else?

379
00:18:41,519 --> 00:18:43,552
No, I...

380
00:18:43,586 --> 00:18:45,686
Do you want me to call someone
about your cats?

381
00:18:45,719 --> 00:18:47,486
Maybe that wom you left
the money to?

382
00:18:47,519 --> 00:18:50,853
I'm sure you want them
to find good homes.

383
00:18:50,886 --> 00:18:52,519
No, don't call her.

384
00:18:52,552 --> 00:18:54,953
I don't want her to see
where I lived.

385
00:18:54,986 --> 00:18:57,653
Somebody else,
call somebody else.

386
00:19:00,086 --> 00:19:02,287
What? Why are you looking
at me like that?

387
00:19:02,320 --> 00:19:03,653
I don't know.

388
00:19:03,686 --> 00:19:06,719
I asked you if you could tell me
anything about your killer

389
00:19:06,753 --> 00:19:08,686
the other day,
and you just disappeared.

390
00:19:08,719 --> 00:19:10,053
I apologize.

391
00:19:10,086 --> 00:19:13,953
I... I was confused.

392
00:19:13,986 --> 00:19:16,053
You are alive
but you could see me.

393
00:19:16,086 --> 00:19:18,387
I didn't understand
about people like you.

394
00:19:18,419 --> 00:19:20,853
I'm sorry if I frightened you.

395
00:19:20,886 --> 00:19:24,152
It's okay.

396
00:19:24,153 --> 00:19:26,220
You look nervous.

397
00:19:26,253 --> 00:19:28,519
I'm not nervous.

398
00:19:30,400 --> 00:19:31,719
It's awfully dark in here.

399
00:19:31,753 --> 00:19:34,786
You afraid someone's
going to see you?

400
00:19:41,053 --> 00:19:43,686
Hey, wait a second,
isn't that her?

401
00:19:43,719 --> 00:19:46,253
Isn't that the woman
we were just talking about,

402
00:19:46,287 --> 00:19:47,886
the one you left
all that money to?

403
00:19:47,920 --> 00:19:51,220
The one who said
that she barely knew you?

404
00:19:51,253 --> 00:19:53,686
Cadence... something?

405
00:19:54,517 --> 00:19:57,230
???

406
00:20:04,900 --> 00:20:07,833
??? ne tonight
as police continue to find

407
00:20:07,866 --> 00:20:09,866
small pieces
of Glendale resident

408
00:20:09,900 --> 00:20:12,400
Vincent DiScala buried
throughout the backyard

409
00:20:12,434 --> 00:20:13,767
of his home.

410
00:20:13,801 --> 00:20:16,434
His wife, Gladys DiScala,
is being taken into custody,

411
00:20:16,467 --> 00:20:18,434
but so far police refuse

412
00:20:18,467 --> 00:20:20,367
to discuss the specifics
of the evidence

413
00:20:20,400 --> 00:20:22,300
against her at this time.

414
00:20:24,100 --> 00:20:26,734
I don't quite know how
I'm going to break this

415
00:20:26,767 --> 00:20:28,367
to poor Bridge.

416
00:20:28,400 --> 00:20:30,467
I don't think we
have enough magnets

417
00:20:30,500 --> 00:20:33,133
to stick this "A+" diorama

418
00:20:33,167 --> 00:20:34,866
depicting the father
of our country

419
00:20:34,900 --> 00:20:36,900
to the refrigerator.

420
00:20:40,866 --> 00:20:42,033
Hmm.

421
00:20:44,434 --> 00:20:46,500
Did I mention the "A+"?

422
00:20:46,534 --> 00:20:48,133
I just don't get it.

423
00:20:48,167 --> 00:20:50,667
Why wouldn't he want to tell me
who did this to him?

424
00:20:50,701 --> 00:20:52,167
Give me a description?

425
00:20:52,200 --> 00:20:54,233
Tell me what really happened?

426
00:20:54,267 --> 00:20:56,767
Because he doesn't
want you to know.

427
00:20:57,866 --> 00:20:59,567
But why?

428
00:20:59,600 --> 00:21:00,933
Why would a person
in their right mind

429
00:21:00,966 --> 00:21:02,833
not want their
killer found?

430
00:21:02,866 --> 00:21:04,567
Don't you find
it mystifying?

431
00:21:04,600 --> 00:21:06,334
Uh, no. What I
find mystifying

432
00:21:06,367 --> 00:21:08,500
is your insistence
on helping this man,

433
00:21:08,534 --> 00:21:10,400
despite the fact that
he doesn't want it.

434
00:21:11,467 --> 00:21:13,233
He's dead.

435
00:21:13,267 --> 00:21:15,167
Let him lie in peace.

436
00:21:15,200 --> 00:21:16,767
For that matr,

437
00:21:16,801 --> 00:21:20,300
how about the two
of us lying in peace?

438
00:21:20,334 --> 00:21:22,701
That makes no sense,
that's crazy.

439
00:21:22,734 --> 00:21:25,367
Why protect the person
who ended your life?

440
00:21:25,400 --> 00:21:26,534
That's crazy?

441
00:21:26,567 --> 00:21:28,966
How about leaving
everything you have

442
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:31,634
